03/09/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha says Albania has become the first country to become free of chemical weapons. Meeting on Saturday (September 1st) with former US Senator Sam Nunn and US Senator Richard Lugar, creators of the so-called Lugar-Nunn Co-operative Threat Reduction programme, Berisha thanked the senators for helping Albania achieve this goal. They are in Tirana to attend a conference on the issue. 
Accompanied by US Ambassador to Tirana John L. Withers ÎÎ, the senators also met with President Bamir Topi and Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu. (Shekulli, Korrieri, Shqip - 02/09/07; Balkanweb, Xinhua - 01/09/07) 
